14. a4 (14. h5 Rc6 $5 (14... O-O 15. Bh3 $1) 15. a4 (15. Bh3 Qa5 16. O-O Nb6
$132) 15... O-O 16. g5 Nf5 $1 17. gxh6 f6 $5 18. hxg7 Rf7 $44) 14... O-O 15.
Bh3 Rc6 $1 (15... f6 16. g5 $14) 16. O-O (16. g5 $6 h5) 16... f6 $1 17. f4 fxe5
18. dxe5 h5 $5 19. gxh5 Nf5 $132) 12... Ne7 13. Nf4 Qc7 14. Qb3 (14. Bd2 O-O-O
$5 15. a4 Nc6 $132) 14... O-O ({As we are going to see, Black has enough
resources to oppose the kingside assault, including the opening of the h-file,
while} 14... O-O-O 15. a4 {is not without risk for him, especially after the
appearance of Bc1 on the a3-f8 diagonal, e.g.} Nc6 16. Ba3 Na5 17. Qb4 $36) 15.
g5 (15. Bd2 Ng6 $1 16. Nxg6 Bxg6 17. h5 Bh7 18. Rc1 {forces} Nb6 {, thus
enabling the break} 19. g5 hxg5 20. h6 gxh6 21. Rxh6 {, but} f6 $132 {
demonstrates that Black has his arguments on the same wing}) 15... hxg5 16.
hxg5 Rfc8 {and Black seems fast enough in his queenside counterplay -} 17. Bd2
Bf5 18. Kf2 Qb6 $132) 9. h5 {Probably the best - White is ruling out the
possible counterstrike h6-h5.} (9. a3 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Nc6 11. Ne2 f6 $132) (9.
Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nc6 (10... h5 $5) 11. Nge2 (11. h5 {transposes to the
leading text}) 11... h5 12. Bg5 Qc7 13. gxh5 f6 14. Bd2 fxe5 15. dxe5 Bxc3 16.
Bxc3 Qf7 $132) 9... Nc6 10. Bd3 Bxd3 11. Qxd3 Bxc3+ $1 $146 ({It is important
to insert this trade instead of} 11... Qb6 {, which allows} 12. Nge2 Nge7 {
as in Paravyan - Abdusattorov, Titled Tuesday 10th Nov, 2020 -} 13. Bd2 $14)
12. bxc3 Qd7 13. Nf3 {White should better watch for the vulnerable c4-square,
otherwise the opponent may obtain a fantastic version of the French Winawer:} (
13. Ne2 Nge7 14. O-O O-O-O $132) (13. a4 Nge7 14. Ra2 Na5 15. f4 O-O-O $132)
13... Nge7 14. Ba3 Na5 $1 15. Nd2 Nc4 $1 {An attractive pawn sacrifice.} (15...
Rc8 {is perhaps a bit slow in the view of} 16. f4 Nc4 17. Nxc4 dxc4 18. Qf3 $14
{Besides, it is still sensible for Black to keep the option for castling to
the long.}) 16. Nxc4 dxc4 17. Qxc4 (17. Qf3 Nd5 18. Bd6 O-O-O $15) 17... O-O
18. O-O b5 19. Qd3 Rac8 $44 {Black has a very human (and sufficient)
compensation.} *

