h4 {This thrust has never been so trendy since the second match Tal -
Botvinnik, 1961, in which The Magician from Riga has used it no less than 5
times. Therefore the whole variation fully deserves to be named after him, in
spite of the fact another unforgettable player - Paul Keres -.has given it
twice a try in the 30's.} h5 {The most principled reply, even though it was
played just once in the mentioned World Championship match.} 5. Bd3 Bxd3 6.
Qxd3 Qa5+ $1 ({The key move - the idea is to disrupt White's main concept for
quick development -} 6... e6 7. Bg5 $1 Qa5+ 8. Nd2 $14) 7. Nc3 ({The most
popular continuation} 7. Nd2 {will be the subject of the next Chapter.}) (7. c3
Qa6 $1 (7... e6 8. a4 $5 Qa6 9. Qd1 {transposes to 8.Qd1 and the minor
alternative 8....e6}) 8. Qd1 (8. Qf3 {may lead to lively positions, for example
} e6 9. b4 $5 (9. a4 c5 10. Na3 $2 Qxa4 $17) 9... Qa4 $1 10. Ne2 (10. Bg5 {
is also answered with the intended} a5 $132) 10... a5 11. bxa5 Rxa5 12. O-O Nd7
({premature is} 12... Qc2 {, as in Mareco - Cori, Mexican op, 2021, because of}
13. a4 $1 $36) 13. Nd2 (13. Bg5 Be7 14. Rc1 Bxg5 15. hxg5 Ne7 $132) 13... b5
14. Nb3 Ra7 15. Nf4 {Here Black can obtain decent play by choosing one of the
alternatives} g6 ({or} 15... Ne7 $5 16. Nxh5 $140 Nxe5 $1 17. Qe2 Nd7 18. Re1
Qc4 19. Qf3 e5 $132) 16. Nd3 Nh6 (16... Ba3 $5 17. Bxa3 Qxa3 18. Nbc5 Nxc5 19.
Nxc5 Ne7 $132 {[%cal Ge7f5]}) 17. Nb2 Qa3 18. c4 Nf5 $1 (18... bxc4 19. Nxc4
Qa4 {J. Burke - J. Liang, Washington, 2022} 20. Bxh6 dxc4 21. Bxf8 $14) 19.
cxb5 cxb5 $132) 8... c5 $1 {A well-timed counterstrike:} ({As mentioned, the
natural} 8... e6 {is a bit slow because of} 9. a4 c5 10. Na3 $1 cxd4 (10... c4
$6 11. b3 $1 Nd7 12. bxc4 Bxa3 13. Bxa3 Qxc4 14. Ne2 $16 {Vokhidov -
Samunenkov, Titled Tuesday 31st May, 2022}) 11. Nb5 Qb6 12. Nxd4 Nc6 13. Ngf3
$36) 9. Ne2 (9. a4 {is less effective here in the view of} cxd4 10. cxd4 e6 11.
Nc3 Nc6 {Black has already fixed the central structure and should not be
afraid of the jump to the b5-square any longer, e.g.} 12. Nf3 (12. Nb5 Qb6 $15)
12... Bb4 $132) 9... e6 10. Nd2 cxd4 11. cxd4 Nh6 {with fine version of the
French -} 12. Nf3 Nf5 13. Bg5 (13. O-O Be7 $11) 13... Qa5+ $1 14. Kf1 Nc6 15.
g3 Be7 $11) (7. Bd2 Qa6 {is essential for the assessment of the early queen
sally:} 8. e6 {is the only decent try -} ({White can unnoticeably get in a
strategically inferior position after} 8. Qxa6 Nxa6 9. e6 f6 $1 {e.g.} 10. Nh3
(10. Bf4 O-O-O 11. Nd2 Nh6 12. Nh3 Nf5 13. Nf3 g6 $15 {Nisipeanu - Rozum,
EU-ch, 2019}) 10... Nh6 11. Nf4 Nf5 12. c3 Nc7 13. Na3 g6 $1 $15 {Isaakidis -
Mis, Larnaca, 2021}) 8... Qxd3 9. exf7+ (9. cxd3 $5 fxe6 10. Nf3 Nd7 11. O-O
Nh6 12. Re1 Nf5 13. Rxe6 Kf7 14. Re2 {Y. Zhou - P. Wells, BCF-chT1c, 2017,
when even} e6 $5 15. Ng5+ Kg8 16. Nxe6 Bd6 $44 {is possible, I would prefer to
play Black}) 9... Kxf7 10. cxd3 Nh6 11. Nf3 Nf5 12. Nc3 (12. Bc3 Ke8 $5 13.
Nbd2 a5 $1 14. a4 g6 15. Nb3 b6 16. Nc1 Bg7 $15 {Kotronias - Atakhan, Caissa
Asli Gp-A Ayvalik, 2022}) (12. O-O e6 13. g3 Nd7 $132) 12... Nd7 {I do not
think that White can pretend for something substantial.} 13. Ne2 (13. O-O-O g6
14. Ne2 Bg7 $15 {and White's static weaknesses has started to tell in M. Adams
- A. Ghasi, Caplin Hastings rapid, 2021}) 13... g6 14. Ng3 {Nakamura -
Fedoseev, Speed Chess Super Swiss, 2020} Bg7 15. Ng5+ Kg8 16. Nxf5 gxf5 17. Bc3
Bf6 18. g3 Nf8 $5 $132) 7... e6 8. Bg5 {The pet move order of Paravyan.} (8.
